noun.description: The European spindle tree, Euonymus europaeus (family Celastraceae), whose dense wood was formerly used for making skewers; the wood of this tree. Compare "prick-timber", "prick tree". Now rare.
The dogwood, Cornus sanguinea. Compare "prick-timber", "prick tree". Now English regional (chiefly southern).

origin: Early 16th century. From prick + wood. Compare prick-timber, prick tree.
